        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): preserve live tool stream order",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nLive WebChat tool cards were reordered incorrectly when a tool event timestamp was older than the assistant stream segment that introduced that tool call. The timestamp-only sorter could place tool cards *before* their causal assistant text.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nThread optional `toolCallId` metadata through the chat stream segment types so the renderer can keep a matching tool card after its causal assistant text, while preserving ordinary timestamp ordering for everything else. `sortChatItemsByVisibleTime` now clamps a tool card's effective sort timestamp to be no earlier than its predecessor stream segment. Adds regression coverage for the delayed/live timestamp race and same-millisecond multi-segment ordering.\n\n## User Impact\nWebChat tool cards now appear in correct causal order — after the assistant text that invoked them — even when the tool event timestamp is slightly earlier than the stream segment timestamp. No behavior change for normal (correctly-ordered) timestamps.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Regression test — fails on `main`, passes with the fix.** For a deterministic sub-millisecond tool/stream ordering race, this fail→pass is the authoritative proof; a live screenshot cannot reliably reproduce the race.\n\nWithout the fix (`ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.ts` reverted to `origin/main`, the new regression tests kept):\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts\n × keeps a live tool card after the stream segment that introduced it\n × keeps same-millisecond stream segments interleaved with their matching tool cards\n Tests  2 failed | 43 passed (45)\n```\n\nWith the fix (PR head `8d7d85f15cba`):\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n Tests  45 passed (45)\n```\n\nVisual ordering is additionally exercised by the e2e test `keeps live assistant stream text before the matching tool card` (`ui/src/ui/e2e/chat-flow.e2e.test.ts`), green in CI.\n\nCI is green on head `8d7d85f15cba`: `build-artifacts`, `check-prod-types`, `check-test-types`, `check-lint`, and all node test shards. Branch is mergeable/clean on latest `main`.\n\nFixes #92122\n",
